#1128: We're all liars, thieves, addicts. We take our happiness for granted until we hurt ourselves, or others. We hold grudges. When faced with the present, we reinvent the past. We're prideful, lustful ... we're incredibly flawed, and eventually our flaws catch up to us.

Heres what I always think about when I go through breakups, and it always helps, so I'm happy to pass it along. 

Somewhere out there, this very moment, the girl that Ill one day marry... is actually out there. The person that Ill hopefully dedicate 50 plus years to, the person who Ill start a family with, the person Ill grow old with, shes actually out there. Alive. This very moment, looking for me just like Im looking for her. Whatever person broke your heart, for whatever reason, is irrelevent in the grand scheme of things. Because the one is out there. And the one, whoever she is, makes up for every shitty break up. 

One day, you will be happy you had to go through this, believe it or not, because without it, you would never be walking down the isle with the one. 

If thats not inspiring, idk what is lol. Feel better stranger! :)

#1111: Shortly before I came to UM my mom remarried to some Eastern European guy named Niko. I don't talk to him much so I was pretty surprised when he called me last week. "You need to talk to James, he's getting out of control". I stood on the line confused. "Uhhh.... who"? I asked. "Your brother.... Nut....". Oh right. My younger brother is deathly allergic to peanuts. In 2nd grade he accidentally had some and had to be taken away in an ambulance. His friends started calling him Nut and it somehow even caught on with my Mother and I. I called my younger brother to get his side of the story. He claimed that Niko had called him last weekend when he was drunk at a friend's house and Niko freaked out about it. Was that really it? Nut is a senior in high school. I wouldn't call drinking at a friends house out of control especially when he doesn't have a car so I knew he wouldn't drive anywhere. I called Niko back. He asks if I talked some sense into him. Depression is a legitimate psychological disorder. It's a flaw in the chemical balances in the brain, and has NOTHING to do with your shortcomings as a person.  You can't just tell someone suffering from depression to change their attitude. That's basically the same as telling someone with cancer to "suck it up".  It just doesn't work that way.

This is extremely offensive and ignorant to assume that people with depression are to blame for suicidal feelings. Maybe some people don't have friends and family to help them get through it and they could be struggling on their own. Suicide is not an easy way out. People struggle with suicidal feelings and try to overcome them, suicide is what happens when people can't do it anymore. But suicide is not cowardly or foolish, it's tragic, and you sound like the fool here.

I don't think you are quite using the right words to describe these suicidal people. Coming from some one who has been there, it is really hard to see how many people around you care about you when you are in such a dark place. On a different note, coming to realize how many people would be devastated by my death kept me from going through with it.
Christ do you think suicidal people don't realize that? when people point this out it only creates guilt and compounds the problem you asshat
You're a piece of shit.
